            <div class="uk-padding-large">
                <p class="uk-h3">Paros</p>
                <p>Successively occupied by Cretans, Minoans, Ionians, Arcadians, Macedonians, Romans, Byzantians and others, who've all made their mark on this large, hilly and fertile island, Paros has been tagged as primarily a ferry hub in recent times. Yet Paros' bustling capital with its ancient remains, the resort town of Naoussa and sweet rural villages are all the more charming for their relative lack of crowds, and there's plenty to do, with good walks, plus excellent windsurfing, kite-surfing and diving.</p>
                <hr>
                <p>Source: <a href="https://www.lonelyplanet.com/greece/cyclades/paros">Lonely Planet</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div id="modal-naxos" class="uk-modal-full" uk-modal>
